## Understanding the Big Bang Theory

The Big Bang theory explains how our entire universe began from a tiny, extremely hot point called a singularity. About 13.8 billion years ago, this point exploded outward, creating space and time itself. This event triggered a rapid cosmic expansion that stretched matter across the vast distances we see today. As the universe cooled, simple particles formed first, then atoms, stars, and galaxies emerged over eons. Scientists developed this idea through careful observation of light from distant stars and the background radiation left behind. It remains our best explanation for everything we observe in the cosmos right now.

